headline.main: AUSTRALIANS SCORE; Veterans of El Alamein Capture New Guinea Base After 10 Days CHARGE BREAKS JAPANESE Germans Easier, Say Victors -- Finschhafen Seizure Puts New Britain in Danger ANOTHER BIG JAPANESE BASE IS CAPTURED AUSTRALIANS SEIZE FINSCHHAFEN BASE

lead_paragraph: ALLIED HEADQUARTERS IN THE SOUTHWEST PACIFIC, Sunday, Oct. 3 -- The bitterly defended air and sea base at Finschhafen in northeast New Guinea was captured at 11 o'clock Saturday morning by Australia's famed Ninth Division in a final charge that drove the Japanese defenders before them.
abstract: Australian troops, supported by US air attacks, take Finschhafen; drive revd; Australians rept Japanese easier foes than Gers in desert; New Brit menaced by Allied control of Huon Gulf; other Australian units reach Ramu River; map; scout planes damage Jap freighter off Kavieng
